"content": "<p>A plant closely associated with cleansing in the OT, being used extensively in rituals for purification.</p>\n<h2>Hyssop associated with cleansing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:2-Ps51:7\">PSA 51:2–51:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:19-Heb9:22\">HEB 9:19–9:22</a></p>\n<h2>Hyssop in religious ritual</h2>\n<h3>At the Passover</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:21-Exod12:25\">EXO 12:21–12:25</a></strong></p>\n<h3>At the slaughter of the red heifer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:1-Num19:10\">NUM 19:1–19:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>In rites of cleansing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:17-Num19:20\">NUM 19:17–19:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:1-Lev14:7\">LEV 14:1–14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:48-Lev14:53\">LEV 14:48–14:53</a></p>\n<h2>Hyssop as a well-known plant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:33\">1KI 4:33</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Hyssop at the crucifixion</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:28-John19:30\">JHN 19:28–19:30</a></strong></p>",
